snippet.textDisplay:
In short: It is a mixed bag. It is good for a JJ movie. Similar to Force
Awakens (you will like this one like that one). Way more original (not
completely because JJ) but suffers from Last Jedi. And yes, mostly
action and mcguffins, nothing deep.



Well. I did have problems with the force awakens, because it was such a
remake with nonsensical things like the resistance and Rey was too much a
mary sue. But there was hope that things will be explained and there
were some cool setups like the knights of Ren. Then Rian made this
horrible movie - the first star wars I can not watch through a second
time - that was as if he hates star wars or the fans or jj abrams or all
three. He ruined everything, changed all the rules of the universe as
if he found it all stupid. This was a huge damage to this trillogy. And
now Rise of Skywalker had to do damage controll. Yes, bringing back the
emperor is not good, they should not have done it even I think they did
it because Rian killed Snoke and they needed a known villain. So the
movie suffers from two things: the damage controll and the abrams style.
But I did like this movie. It was the best of the trillogy for me
because it was not just a remake. Many things that made no sense happend
because Rian did not further the story but destroyed it. They had no
time to explain things and it is really sad because here you see that it
could have been a good trillogy. Not a great one, a great looking one.
There were good ideas, like the defecting storm troopers. And even if JJ
only recylcles stuff - which is sad because I would enjoy original
stories more - I think here you can see that JJ can do a good recyling
job. And I think they even tried to listen to complaints. There was some
romance in this movie. Rey did loose and showed weakness. Fin was
heroic. And so on. If you think, JJ only teases stuff and makes mystery
boxes without knowing whats in them, I had the feeling that JJ really
had some ideas and tried to pack them all into this two hours. So again.
If you think about that JJ had to do all this damage controll, he did a
fine job BUT he did it JJ style. So what can you expect. I like to say,
that JJ should not have made a remake but Rian killed Star Wars and
now JJ brought it back, but it is still in the hosbital as JJ is not the
best doctor (but even the best doctor could not have safed the
trillogy, just make Star Wars less sick after the reanimation).

snippet.textDisplay:
In trying to make rey the ultimate hero.
They made kylo ren actually quite likable.
Broken Confused and being less powerful.

I mean more likable then all other newly introduced characters.
He was like his grandfather after all.

You know its hard to fix the damage already done but here's what could have been done -

Instead of Kylo ren being visited by Han, he should have been visited by Anakin's force ghost who speaks with him and makes him realize that even he - Vader also turned at the end and brings him to the light side.

At the final battle it would have been more tragic and emotional if Rey would have died heroically fighting Palpatine and this to let injured Ben Solo to desperately and helplessly call for help from all the jedis.

It could have been shown Anakin's force ghost appearing behind Ben/Kylo that would have made Palpatine uncomfortable. Then Luke, Obiwan, Mace windu, Yoda with many others all standing behind Ben Solo smiling as Anakin says a thousand generation of Jedis are with you... as Palpatine losses his Calm.

Rey could have completed the sacrificng arc thus proving she isnt like Palpatine at all, bringing a bitter sweet ending to her story which could have made her more likable.

And Ben Solo could have completed his arch by truly following on the footsteps of his grandfather and by bringing balance to the force.

Also it would have made the title more meaningful - Rise of Skywalker as Ben Solo was also Leia Skywalker's Son.
It would have been great to see him being alone and grieving after the victory visiting tatooine where his Master Luke lived and where his grandfather was born.

snippet.textDisplay: Did I just see the same SW movie as my fave critics on Youtube who didn't like it? I though it was a blast!While it was choppy at the beginning, and it was definitely overcrowded with characters, it all came beautifully together by the ending.  I thought it was an impossible task to fix all the mistakes of TLJ, but JJ Abrams did it! He managed to make a film that I actually cared about, which is a huge achievement after Ryan Johnson's mess. This was an epic, action-packed adventure as all SW movies should be, and the ending was definitely moving for me. And I'll definitely see it again too! I'd say if you didn't like TLJ, don't miss this one, you will most likely be thrilled.

snippet.textDisplay: It is so unfortunate. TFA was a fine enough movie (I think it is one of the better in the series. Better than I-III and VI IMO). Not a perfect film by any means, but did good enough to get SW back on a positive trajectory. Then, TLJ happened and just fucked everything from a narrative perspective. I will never understand what Johnson was thinking. He treated TLJ like it was a standalone film and not the second film of a trilogy. Rise of Skywalker was D.O.A and never really had much of a chance to succeed. In 2.5 hours there is no way to dig out of the hole that Johnson dug.
